%p
  Dear #{@recipient.ops_first_name},
- if @workshop.program_type == 6
  %p
    We’re looking forward to seeing you at your #{@workshop.phase_info[:long_name]} workshop on #{@workshop.segments.first.start.strftime("%A, %B %d")}! Together with your peers and facilitators, you’ll gain the support and resources you need to make a difference at your school.
- else
  %p
    We’re looking forward to seeing you at your #{@workshop.phase_info[:long_name]} workshop on #{@workshop.segments.first.start.strftime("%A, %B %d")}! Together with your peers and facilitators, you’ll gain the support and resources you need to make a difference in your classroom.
%p
  As part of your commitment to this program, you are expected to participate in this workshop. If you have any conflicts with these dates, please email
  %a{href:'mailto:pd@code.org'}
    pd@code.org
  If you have questions, check out our
  %a{href:'https:' + CDO.code_org_url("/educate/pd/15-16/faq")}
    FAQ
  or send us an email.
- # If phase 2 or 4, or 3A for CSinS or CSinA, and not program_type 6 (counselor/admin)
- if (@workshop.phase == 2 || @workshop.phase == 8 || (@workshop.phase == 4 && (@workshop.program_type == 1 || @workshop.program_type == 2))) && (@workshop.program_type != 6)
  = render partial: 'prerequisite_information', locals: {workshop: @workshop}
  %ul
    %li
      %p
        Check your progress in Code Studio by clicking the orange button in the top-right corner and selecting Code Studio from the drop down. Then select the PD course you are enrolled in.
      %p
        %em
          Here’s what a successful online PD looks like. All the progress circles are green.
      %img{src:"#{CDO.studio_url(image_url('finished_pd_script.jpg'), 'https:')}", style:'width: 600px'}
      %p
        The number of stages/levels may differ from the above image.
    %li
      Payment: To be paid, you must complete all the circles in your Code Studio progress bar for the phase and program. Completion is indicated by a green circle (see example below). You will be paid once ALL portions of this PD segment are completed.

%h2
  Workshops Details
%p
  See below or visit code.org/pd for your in-person workshop details and bookmark for future use!
%h3
  Dates and times
- @workshop.segments.each do |segment|
  %p
    #{segment.start.strftime("%A, %B %d, %Y")}
    %br
    #{segment.start.strftime("%I:%M %P")} - #{segment.end.strftime("%I:%M %P")}
%h3
  Location
%p
  #{@workshop[:location]}
%h3
  Catering
%p
  Breakfast and lunch will be served every day. We will offer vegetarian options, but please plan to bring your own meal or eat responsibly if you have any other dietary restrictions or food allergies.
%h3
  What to bring
- if @workshop.phase == 2
  -if @workshop.program_type == 3
    %p
      Laptop (optional), water bottle, and snacks
  -else
    %p
      Laptop and charger, water bottle, and snacks
- elsif @workshop.phase >= 4 && @workshop.phase <= 8
  -if @workshop.program_type == 3
    %p
      Curriculum guide, green journal, laptop and charger, water bottle, and snacks
  -else
    %p
      Curriculum guide, laptop and charger, water bottle, and snacks
-if @workshop.instructions
  %h3
    Notes
  %p
    #{@workshop.instructions}
%p
  See you soon,
%br
  The Code.org PD team
